<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1514,1935]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,616,1550,1575]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">
Condition of the 
<typeStatus box="[411,475,1550,1575]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">types</typeStatus>
. 
<typeStatus box="[491,611,1550,1575]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">Lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Forewings somewhat rubbed. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[976,1159,1550,1575]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">
<typeStatus box="[976,1154,1550,1575]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">Paralectotypes</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
One of the males from 
<date box="[151,320,1586,1611]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" value="1927-07-11" valueMax="1927-07-20" valueMin="1927-07-11">
<number box="[151,222,1586,1611]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" value="15.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="11.0">11–20</number>
.vii. 
<number box="[261,320,1586,1611]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" value="1927.0">1927</number>
</date>
has the apex of forewings badly rubbed, almost without the white scales that characterise the species. One of the specimens from 
<date box="[564,733,1622,1647]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" value="1927-07-21" valueMax="1927-07-31" valueMin="1927-07-21">
<number box="[564,635,1622,1647]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" value="26.0" valueMax="31.0" valueMin="21.0">21–31</number>
.vii. 
<number box="[674,733,1622,1647]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" value="1927.0">1927</number>
</date>
has lost its abdomen. Another from the same date has lost its left antenna. All others have only minor rubbing on the forewings.
</paragraph>
