<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="515" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1514,1935]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1694,1719]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from 
<number box="[692,720,1695,1719]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" value="12.0">12</number>
<typeStatus box="[727,828,1695,1719]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">syntypes</typeStatus>
, all from Fazenda Taperinha. The specimens collected in July and August are deposited at the 
<collectionCode box="[629,722,1731,1754]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/91g3-0mnw" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">NHMW</collectionCode>
. The remaining two could not be traced. Because they were collected by Hagmann, it was logical to think that they might be held at the Museu Paraense Emílio Goeldi, but William Overal, present curator of 
<taxonomicName box="[543,678,1802,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Acanthopteroctetidae;Agathiphagidae;Alucitidae;Tineodidae;Axiidae;Axiidae;Calocarididae;Micheleidae;Strahlaxiidae;Bombycidae;Brahmaeidae;Carthaeidae;Endromidae;Eupterotidae;Lemoniidae;Mirinidae;Saturniidae;Sphingidae;Callidulidae;Choreutidae;Carposinidae;Copromorphidae;Cossidae;Dudgeoneidae;Drepanidae;Epicopeiidae;Epermeniidae;Eriocraniidae;Galacticidae;Agonoxenidae;Batrachedridae;Blastobasidae;Coleophoridae;Cosmopterigidae;Elachistidae;Ethmiidae;Gelechiidae;Holcopogonidae;Lecithoceridae;Metachandidae;Momphidae;Oecophoridae;Pterolonchidae;Scythrididae;Symmocidae;Geometridae;Sematuridae;Uraniidae;Bucculatricidae;Douglasiidae;Gracillariidae;Roeslerstammiidae;Hedylidae;Anomosetidae;Hepialidae;Neotheoridae;Palaeosetidae;Prototheoridae;Hesperiidae;Heterobathmiidae;Hyblaeidae;Immidae;Adelidae;Cecidosidae;Crinopterygidae;Heliozelidae;Incurvariidae;Prodoxidae;Anthelidae;Lasiocampidae;Lophocoronidae;Micropterigidae;Mimallonidae;Mnesarchaeidae;Neopseustidae;Nepticulidae;Opostegidae;Arctiidae;Doidae;Lymantriidae;Noctuidae;Nolidae;Notodontidae;Oenosandridae;Pantheidae;Palaephatidae;Lycaenidae;Nymphalidae;Papilionidae;Pieridae;Riodinidae;Pterophoridae;Crambidae;Pyralidae;Schreckensteiniidae;Brachodidae;Castniidae;Sesiidae;Simaethistidae;Thyrididae;Acrolophidae;Arrhenophanidae;Eriocottidae;Psychidae;Tineidae;Tischeriidae;Tortricidae;Urodidae;Whalleyanidae;Acrolepiidae;Bedelliidae;Glyphipterigidae;Heliodinidae;Lyonetiidae;Plutellidae;Yponomeutidae;Ypsolophidae;Aididae;Anomoeotidae;Chrysopolomidae;Cyclotornidae;Dalceridae;Epipyropidae;Heterogynidae;Himantopteridae;Lacturidae;Limacodidae;Megalopygidae;Somabrachyidae;Zygaenidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
of that institution, found no specimens with compatible labels.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1514,1935]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">
The 
<typeStatus box="[252,354,1838,1863]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">lectotype</typeStatus>
by present designation is the specimen here illustrated. In relation to the 
<typeStatus box="[1201,1355,1838,1863]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">paralectotype</typeStatus>
, which bears exactly the same labels, it can be distinguished by having the wings slightly more worn, and by the position of the antennae.
</paragraph>
